1. to float; to set afloat; to launch 彼は小さな船を水に浮かべている。He is sailing a little boat on the water.
2. to show on one's face (smile, sadness, etc.) 怪物は残酷な微笑みを浮かべた。The monster's smile was cruel.
3. to recall; to call to mind; to imagine; to think of

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'bu' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 1. to float; to be suspended １枚の落ち葉が水面に浮かんでいた。A fallen leaf floated on the surface of the water.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'bu' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 2. to rise to the surface; to appear; to emerge; to show up; to loom (up) 浮かんだと思うとまた沈む。Now it rises, now it sinks.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'bu' ending, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 3. to come to mind; to have inspiration ２週間新しいプロジェクトについて考えていましたが、よい考えが浮かびませんでした。I had been thinking about our new project for two weeks, but I couldn't come up with a good idea.
浮ぶ 【うかぶ】、泛ぶ 【うかぶ】、泛かぶ 【うかぶ】
